(Finding #4: [High] Multiple quantity_of calls in collateral.spend may allow) Tj T*
(  double-counting) Tj T*
(  Detector: quantity-of-double-counting) Tj T*
(  Module: collateral) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/collateral.ak:24) Tj T*
(Description: Handler collateral.spend calls `quantity_of` 12 times to check asset) Tj T*
(    quantities. Without verifying mutual exclusivity, an attacker may satisfy multiple) Tj T*
(    checks with overlapping assets.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Use `value.tokens` or `value.without_lovelace` for exact value matching) Tj T*
(    instead of multiple independent quantity_of checks.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(Finding #5: [Medium] Incomplete Value check via quantity_of in collateral.spend) Tj T*
(  Detector: incomplete-value-extraction) Tj T*
(  Module: collateral) Tj T*
(  Location: validators/collateral.ak:24) Tj T*
(Description: Handler collateral.spend uses quantity_of to check specific asset quantities) Tj T*
(    but doesn't validate the full Value. Other native assets may be drained.) Tj T*
(Recommendation: Complement quantity_of checks with assets.match for full Value validation.) Tj T*
